In React, hooks are functions that allow you to add state and other React features to functional components. 
The useState hook is one of the most commonly used hooks in React and provides a way to add state variables 
to your functional components without the need for class components.

The useState hook is used to declare state variables and get their current values. It takes an initial value 
as an argument and returns an array with two elements: the current state value and a function to update that state. 
The syntax for using the useState hook looks like the provided code.
